[SN]TITLE[SN]
Scottish League Two: Clyde 3-1 Stirling Albion

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
David Marsh scored twice as Clyde defeated 10-man Stirling Albion to finish third in Scottish League Two and qualify for the promotion play-offs.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Stirling's Sean Dickson headed narrowly wide before Marsh drilled home following Scott Linton's corner.
Marsh headed in from Ross Millen's cross and David Gormley fired Clyde's third from close range.
Stirling's Ross Smith was shown a straight red card with 25 minutes left, but Scott Burns fired a reply.
Victory lifted Clyde above Queen's Park, who lost to Annan Athletic, into third place, meaning a play-off semi-final against Elgin City.
